        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior CFD and experimental hemolysis studies spanning 2008–2022, consolidating power-law damage accumulation models, validated shear-stress thresholds, and published NIH benchmarks from at least seven independent research groups. This synthesis informed the turbulence model selection, hemolysis power-law exponent calibration, and acceptance threshold of RH < 1 used in the current COU. The consolidated evidence base represents the state of the art in computational hemolysis prediction for rotary blood pumps."
